{
  "texts": [
    "Essentially, DL algorithms are based on neural networks.Prediction, classification, and other functions are carried out by the neurons in multiple layers of a neural network.",
    "Each neuron's output is sent to the neurons in the next layer, where it is tweaked until reaching the final output layer Fig. 1.",
    "In the neural network, the Initial data for the neural network is in the input layer.",
    "Hidden layers are between the input and output layers, which serve as the hub for all computing.",
    "The output layer generates the outcome given the inputs."
  ]
}